# bar-metrics — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in real values. Never commit secrets;
# `.env*` is gitignored (this `.env.example` is the one tracked exception).
#
# The app skeleton (issue #2) needs NO environment variables to boot — this file
# documents the pattern and lists the variables later slices will introduce so
# the runbook stays one source of truth.

# --- Later slices (NOT required to run the skeleton) ---

# Neon application database — app-owned tables, later Auth.js sessions
# (issue #4 / ADR 0003). Two URLs to the same Neon database:
#   - DATABASE_URL: POOLED (PgBouncer) connection — used by the app at runtime
#     (serverless-safe). Its host contains "-pooler".
#   - DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED: DIRECT (unpooled) connection — used only by Prisma
#     Migrate (PgBouncer's transaction pooling breaks migrations).
# The Neon/Vercel integration injects both names automatically; `vercel env
# pull` writes them into `.env.local`.
# DATABASE_URL=
# DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED=

# Read-only connection to the legacy nubebar Postgres read-model (issue #5 / ADR 0003).
# NUBEBAR_DATABASE_URL=

# Anthropic API key for the tool-calling chatbot (ADR 0001 / 0004).
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
